Female reproductive system. ( Fig. 3 A–D) Ventral channel marked, vestibule not developed. Lower oviduct gland ( LOG ) longer than high. Bursa copulatrix ( BC ) relatively large, about half size of lower oviduct gland; seminal receptacle ( SR ) small, elongated, not found in all studied specimens. Upper oviduct gland (
UOG
) coiled, usually short lobes ( L) visible (these probably involved in sperm storage).

Distribution .
Pusillina tumidula
has been reported from Iceland , and Faeroe, Norwegian, Barents, White and Kara Seas including the waters around Svalbard and Franz Joseph Land ( Golikov 1987 ; Warén 1996 ;
Golikov et al . 2001
;
Sneli et al . 2005
; Nekhaev 2014 ). Study of ZIN collections shows that records of that species from the Bering Sea (Kantor & Sysoev 2006 ;
Sirenko et al. 2013
) are based on mis-identification of the another rissoid species.
